Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:31.080 --> 01:32.673
(RUSTLING)

02:53.400 --> 02:55.232
(CART RUMBLES)

03:01.680 --> 03:04.035
Whoa, boy. Whoa. Steady.

03:06.120 --> 03:08.111
(DRIVER COUGHS)

03:11.480 --> 03:12.515
Morning, Mr Sumner.

03:13.680 --> 03:15.273
(COUGHS)

03:16.880 --> 03:18.439
Are you feeling any better?

03:22.080 --> 03:23.150
Fat ones today.

03:23.280 --> 03:24.600
(SIGHS)

03:24.720 --> 03:26.518
Aye.

03:29.160 --> 03:30.434
(COUGHS)

03:34.760 --> 03:35.989
Mr Sumner,

03:36.120 --> 03:37.918
um...

03:40.040 --> 03:41.360
I got some jam.

03:41.480 --> 03:42.595
It's blackcurrant.

03:43.840 --> 03:45.353
I've got plenty-

03:46.680 --> 03:48.751
It's time for market.

03:48.880 --> 03:50.075
Morning to ye.

03:53.520 --> 03:55.318
<i>Yah, yah, yah, yah, yah,</i>

03:55.440 --> 03:57.113
<i>I '</i>

03:58.160 --> 03:59.309
Hup.

04:04.640 --> 04:05.994
Come on.

04:06.120 --> 04:08.031
Good boy.

04:08.160 --> 04:10.071
Good boy, good boy. Go on. Go on.

04:53.880 --> 04:55.791
(ALARM CLOCK RINGS)

05:05.720 --> 05:08.189
(FOX SCREECH ES)

05:15.240 --> 05:17.311
(DAWN CHORUS)

05:58.000 --> 05:59.957
(SUMNER COUGHS)

06:15.520 --> 06:16.999
Tinned peaches.

06:18.760 --> 06:20.990
Some lemonade.

06:25.640 --> 06:26.869
Edmund Reid.

06:28.440 --> 06:29.430
Gustus, have you...?

06:29.560 --> 06:30.834
Not yet.

06:30.960 --> 06:32.792
He is hunted.

06:34.320 --> 06:35.390
Potted meat.

06:35.520 --> 06:37.750
Apples.

06:40.320 --> 06:41.310
Cheese.

06:44.640 --> 06:47.712
He has borne your sins
for the world, Nathaniel.

06:47.840 --> 06:49.319
How it has to be, brother.

06:57.880 --> 06:59.200
Mr Sumner, he's...

07:00.960 --> 07:02.792
...he's not called for his eels.

07:02.920 --> 07:05.309
Perhaps he has no want for 'em today.

07:05.440 --> 07:07.795
He told me his cottage
was just downriver.

07:11.280 --> 07:12.429
I thought, erm...

07:14.600 --> 07:16.910
I thought to take his eels to him.

07:17.040 --> 07:19.111
He has been poorly, you see.

07:19.240 --> 07:20.958
Did you, now?

07:22.680 --> 07:23.715
Gustus...

07:25.440 --> 07:29.957
...since I've been here, I've not
seen a single soul but Mr Sumner.

07:30.080 --> 07:34.313
This life here, it is only until
Edmund Reid is reckoned for.

07:34.440 --> 07:37.193
But until then, it is the best life
I can make for you.

07:37.320 --> 07:39.914
You have done me a kindness,
Gustus, I know it,

07:40.040 --> 07:41.713
but he will be reckoned for when?

07:41.840 --> 07:43.274
Reid is hunted and will be found.

07:43.400 --> 07:46.074
But while he puts his snout to
the very cobbles of Whitechapel

07:46.200 --> 07:49.158
for scent of you and sniffs at
who knows what trail beyond,

07:49.280 --> 07:52.113
it is best you keep to yourself,
is it not?

07:54.680 --> 07:56.956
I shall bring books for you.

08:00.120 --> 08:02.873
You might visit with...with the pup.

08:04.040 --> 08:05.155
The Pup?

08:05.280 --> 08:06.793
Yeah, your boy Connor.

08:06.920 --> 08:08.718
Makes him my nephew, does it not?

08:11.840 --> 08:13.353
Come to the house tonight.

08:14.400 --> 08:15.356
Dinner.

08:15.480 --> 08:16.550
Hm.

08:16.680 --> 08:17.909
I'll collect you.

08:20.080 --> 08:24.233
Mr Sumner shall come for his eels
tomorrow, I have no doubt.

08:26.760 --> 08:28.080
No need trouble him before.

08:56.280 --> 08:58.430
It's good food, Gustus.

08:59.800 --> 09:00.915
Very good.

09:09.680 --> 09:11.796
- Here.
- No!

09:13.880 --> 09:16.076
Leave him be, Nathaniel.

09:18.800 --> 09:21.394
The pup needs help, is all.

09:27.840 --> 09:28.875
Look.

09:29.920 --> 09:32.753
It's like this...

09:32.880 --> 09:33.915
YOU see?

09:35.240 --> 09:37.834
The hunger...

09:37.960 --> 09:38.950
Gustus.

09:42.280 --> 09:43.998
There are days I feel it...

09:45.600 --> 09:46.590
...abate...

09:50.480 --> 09:52.312
...and then it is there...

09:55.400 --> 09:57.073
...blade catching glint...

09:59.640 --> 10:01.551
...black in my blood again.

10:03.480 --> 10:04.629
Do you think...

10:06.600 --> 10:09.240
Do you think some day
it will have gone?

10:11.200 --> 10:13.794
Yes, brother.

10:13.920 --> 10:15.433
I want to be better...

10:16.680 --> 10:18.830
...Gustus.

10:18.960 --> 10:23.033
There are doctors of the mind,
Nathaniel.

10:25.040 --> 10:27.190
After Reid is done with,

10:27.320 --> 10:29.550
we will see the finest.

10:31.160 --> 10:32.639
Thank you, Gustus.

10:46.800 --> 10:49.952
Every day we spend imprisoned here...

10:52.000 --> 10:55.834
...the streets beyond these walls
turn fiercer against us...

10:58.120 --> 11:02.990
...every resident of this borough
made into Shine's henchman.

11:04.120 --> 11:06.077
Oh, this ain't a jail, Reid.

11:07.920 --> 11:08.910
In jail, you get more sunlight.

11:09.040 --> 11:11.680
My playhouse is not
your wastebasket, Mr Reid,

11:11.800 --> 11:13.632
and if jail seems preferable, Captain,

11:13.760 --> 11:16.195
do please feel most free
to relocate yourself.

11:16.320 --> 11:18.391
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

11:25.280 --> 11:27.237
(LATCH CLICKS)

11:29.680 --> 11:31.478
(DOOR CREAKS)

11:31.600 --> 11:32.954
(GUN COCKS)

11:34.320 --> 11:35.276
Howdy, Thatcher.

11:35.400 --> 11:37.676
You have something?
Tell me you have something.

11:37.800 --> 11:39.996
I searched reports of murders,
of woundings.

11:40.120 --> 11:42.509
There's naught so much as
resembles the animal method.

11:42.640 --> 11:44.438
He...he has not killed again.

11:44.560 --> 11:48.633
Well, maybe, erm... Well, maybe
Dove finally put him in the ground,

11:48.760 --> 11:50.876
you know, to...to protect himself.

11:51.000 --> 11:54.959
No. No, the bond between them.
He would not. I know it.

11:55.080 --> 11:56.878
She's right.

11:57.000 --> 11:59.276
You could have warned us
about the bounty, Thatcher.

11:59.400 --> 12:02.631
Shine don't confide in me
his stratagems, Captain.

12:02.760 --> 12:06.037
The first I heard of it...was this.

12:06.160 --> 12:08.436
This is a hell of an informant
we have, huh?

12:08.560 --> 12:09.880
MY apologies.

12:11.480 --> 12:16.111
Sergeant Thatcher, your efforts are
invaluable and we are grateful for them.

12:16.240 --> 12:17.799
Oh, eternally so.

12:20.720 --> 12:22.279
Best make my way.

12:28.640 --> 12:29.755
(DOG BARKS)

12:29.880 --> 12:31.837
Do you imagine
making the boy feel an ass

12:31.960 --> 12:34.076
will inspire loyalty and diligence?

12:34.200 --> 12:37.192
Perhaps you should leave
managing policemen to me.

12:37.320 --> 12:40.199
If we have need
of an informant in a brothel,

12:40.320 --> 12:43.278
I have no doubt your expertise
will prove invaluable.

12:43.400 --> 12:46.552
You may not think me ally, but we are
nonetheless, for now, cellmates.

12:46.680 --> 12:48.876
Miss Hart, do you
not understand why...?

12:49.000 --> 12:51.594
Oh, I understand more than you can know,
Mr Reid,

12:51.720 --> 12:55.315
and I have given you my word I will
make it right with your daughter.

12:55.440 --> 12:58.114
I will make it right.

13:06.560 --> 13:07.709
Mr Sumner?

13:16.720 --> 13:18.711
Sorry, erm...

13:20.280 --> 13:21.190
...is he here?

13:21.320 --> 13:25.553
My father, he had been poorly
for some time.

13:27.080 --> 13:28.514
Oh.

13:28.640 --> 13:29.960
I brought eels.

13:31.920 --> 13:34.912
Yes, you did. Wanting pay, then?

13:35.040 --> 13:37.554
No. Money? No, no.

13:37.680 --> 13:39.512
Erm, it's just...

13:43.800 --> 13:45.552
Take the eels.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.831
(GASPING)

13:53.080 --> 13:55.356
Caleb. Robin.

13:56.880 --> 13:57.870
Mr...

13:58.920 --> 14:00.991
Nathaniel.

14:02.600 --> 14:05.911
...Nathaniel fished our eels.
Wishes to pay respects.

14:10.480 --> 14:12.391
Dig, boy-

14:13.960 --> 14:15.837
(GROANS)

14:15.960 --> 14:17.792
I can help with that.

14:48.560 --> 14:49.709
Thank you, Nathaniel.

14:51.240 --> 14:53.277
May we offer you supper?

14:53.400 --> 14:54.390
No.

14:55.720 --> 14:56.994
I must be getting back.

14:57.120 --> 15:01.000
It's no banquet
but there is stew and potato,

15:01.120 --> 15:02.872
a full belly for your hard work.

15:10.440 --> 15:11.760
Thank you.

15:28.440 --> 15:31.239
You're the man of the house now,
Caleb,

15:31.360 --> 15:33.033
and of the business.

15:33.160 --> 15:34.195
I'll need help, Pru.

15:34.320 --> 15:35.879
Of course.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.879
A family pulls together,
does it not, Robin?

15:39.000 --> 15:41.879
You'll help your uncle, won't you?

15:42.000 --> 15:44.640
- CALEB: Pour the gin, boy.
- Yes, Uncle.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.831
Good lad.

15:56.680 --> 15:59.559
Father used to go upriver
for his eels.

15:59.680 --> 16:03.469
Then you appeared overnight,
like a toadstool.

16:07.600 --> 16:09.318
Oh, I, erm...

16:09.440 --> 16:10.839
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

16:12.600 --> 16:14.557
...I used to live by another river.

16:16.560 --> 16:18.597
How did you come upon the cottage?

16:18.720 --> 16:20.631
It was abandoned, I thought.

16:20.760 --> 16:22.080
Erm...

16:24.280 --> 16:25.839
...my brother.

16:25.960 --> 16:28.474
PRUDENCE: A brother?
Does he fish also?

16:28.600 --> 16:30.637
No, he is, erm...

16:30.760 --> 16:31.989
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

16:33.320 --> 16:35.630
He's far away.

16:35.760 --> 16:37.876
Took a ship west.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.513
Our father, see, he, erm...

16:40.960 --> 16:42.439
He...he died.

16:45.920 --> 16:48.753
Then let us say a prayer
for both our fathers.

16:52.040 --> 16:54.031
May they rest at peace.

16:57.480 --> 16:59.869
Now eat up, all of you.

17:03.880 --> 17:05.598
(BOTTLE UNCORKED)

17:05.720 --> 17:07.676
(DRINK POURS)

17:09.079 --> 17:10.832
(CART RUMBLES)

17:22.440 --> 17:23.760
Miss Sumner.

17:26.599 --> 17:28.876
Excuse my lateness, Nathaniel.

17:29.000 --> 17:33.153
My brother Caleb is
not well this morning.

17:33.280 --> 17:36.511
- (COINS CLINK)
- Mama, did you ask him?

17:36.640 --> 17:38.278
Robin, please.

17:40.640 --> 17:43.314
Nathaniel, without Caleb, I..

17:44.360 --> 17:47.239
Robin and I shall struggle to
manage the stall by ourselves.

17:47.360 --> 17:49.749
If there was any way you could...

17:49.880 --> 17:54.556
I mean to say, there'd be
coin in it, of course.

17:55.720 --> 17:56.630
Selling fish?

17:56.760 --> 17:57.830
Yes, sir.

18:00.680 --> 18:02.159
In Whitechapel?

18:03.520 --> 18:04.954
I should not.

18:06.160 --> 18:08.151
- Whitechapel, it's...
- No matter.

18:10.200 --> 18:12.953
We shall manage, shan't we, Robin?

18:15.440 --> 18:17.078
Good day, Nathaniel.

18:21.440 --> 18:22.635
Miss Sumner!

18:34.160 --> 18:36.037
You're a quiet one, aren't you?

18:38.160 --> 18:39.434
What should I say?

18:40.680 --> 18:42.796
Most folk talk too much.

18:48.480 --> 18:49.629
The, erm...

18:50.840 --> 18:52.672
...the boy's father?

18:54.840 --> 18:56.831
The typhus.

18:56.960 --> 18:59.236
Robin was barely born.

19:00.280 --> 19:02.430
I had practice enough at mothering,
though.

19:02.560 --> 19:04.517
Mine died bearing Caleb.

19:04.640 --> 19:07.871
Caleb was my babe
before Robin came along.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.718
Caleb wailed when Robin was born.

19:09.840 --> 19:12.309
Think he thought he'd lose me too.

19:16.120 --> 19:17.838
Every boy needs their mother.

19:21.520 --> 19:23.591
(METAL BANGS)

19:24.640 --> 19:26.870
(VENDORS SHOUT)

19:27.000 --> 19:29.355
Nathaniel, can you help
with the brazier?

19:36.040 --> 19:38.600
(VENDORS SHOUT)

19:50.040 --> 19:52.919
Fresh fish! Fresh fish!

19:53.040 --> 19:55.395
Best in Whitechapel!

19:55.520 --> 19:58.399
Fresh fish! Fresh fish!

19:58.520 --> 20:01.273
Eels and pike and carp and perch!

20:03.040 --> 20:04.235
Fresh fish!

20:04.360 --> 20:05.714
Morning, Inspector. The usual?

20:05.840 --> 20:08.514
This stall 'ere, no eels better.

20:08.640 --> 20:10.756
Two portion of eels,
if you please, lad.

20:10.880 --> 20:13.315
Coming up, Mr Thatcher.

20:16.800 --> 20:18.393
Fresh fish!

20:19.760 --> 20:21.558
Fresh fish!

20:21.680 --> 20:23.273
THATCHER: Much obliged, lad.

20:23.400 --> 20:26.153
- All well today, Mr Thatcher?
- Yeah, Robin. All well.

20:26.280 --> 20:29.033
It's just, erm...
police business, is all.

20:29.160 --> 20:31.037
See you tomorrow, Mr Thatcher.

20:32.680 --> 20:34.318
Will you wrap this tail for me,
please, Nathaniel?

20:34.440 --> 20:37.592
Fresh fish! Fresh fish!

20:37.720 --> 20:42.999
Eels and pike and carp and perch,
best in Whitechapel!

20:44.200 --> 20:45.713
Fresh fish!

20:53.040 --> 20:54.872
Thank you for your help, Nathaniel.

20:55.920 --> 20:57.991
If you have need
of a little extra coin,

20:58.120 --> 21:00.316
we have need
for an extra pair of hands.

21:01.360 --> 21:04.398
- Happy to help.
- Then we're both happy.

21:10.760 --> 21:11.955
Walk on.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.918
(VENDORS SHOUT)

21:29.280 --> 21:32.432
- Let Nathaniel do that.
- I always chop for the stew.

21:32.560 --> 21:34.949
I need you out front till Robin's back
from the knife-sharpener.

21:35.080 --> 21:37.276
Nathaniel's a quicker blade.

21:44.320 --> 21:48.314
Carp and eels! Pike and perch!
Who wants a good fish supper?

21:55.320 --> 21:56.390
Four pence.

21:58.600 --> 21:59.999
(COINS CLINK)

22:03.440 --> 22:05.351
Always overcharge the bloody Hebrews.

22:11.240 --> 22:13.231
Carp and eels!

22:13.360 --> 22:14.680
Carp and eels!

22:14.800 --> 22:16.791
(CLOCK TICKS)

22:45.840 --> 22:47.831
For flavour.

22:52.000 --> 22:55.277
No! Stop! He's snatched the money!

22:55.400 --> 22:57.038
(GASPS)

23:07.320 --> 23:09.596
-(GROANS)
- This man?

23:10.680 --> 23:11.875
Money.

23:12.000 --> 23:13.991
Money!

23:18.080 --> 23:20.071
- (BONES CRUNCH)
- (SCREAMS)

23:26.240 --> 23:29.756
What's afoot 'ere?
Oi! Back here with you!

23:29.880 --> 23:32.633
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- Go on, get after him!

23:48.560 --> 23:49.789
Nathaniel?

23:54.680 --> 23:55.909
You left this.

23:57.280 --> 23:59.271
Thank you, Robin.

24:00.520 --> 24:01.510
Here.

24:07.880 --> 24:09.393
Why did you go?

24:11.440 --> 24:12.714
I was, erm...

24:17.360 --> 24:19.351
I was afraid, boy.

24:22.680 --> 24:25.069
But you're strong.

24:26.800 --> 24:29.110
- That's silly.
- (SCOFFS)

24:39.320 --> 24:41.960
Is this where you fish the eels?

24:42.080 --> 24:43.229
Mm-hm.

24:47.360 --> 24:48.589
Will you show me?

24:54.040 --> 24:56.395
Now, right...

24:57.840 --> 24:59.592
(GRUNTS)

24:59.720 --> 25:01.597
...hands, please.

25:02.800 --> 25:05.394
There you are. There.

25:05.520 --> 25:07.477
There you are.

25:08.560 --> 25:11.074
Now, you put the bait in there.

25:12.360 --> 25:14.351
There you are.

25:20.800 --> 25:22.950
Oh! (CHUCKLES)

25:23.080 --> 25:26.277
He's a slippery fella, ain't he?
(CHUCKLES)

25:26.400 --> 25:27.754
Right.

25:27.880 --> 25:29.678
Robin? Robin.

25:31.560 --> 25:32.709
Get yourself home.

25:37.880 --> 25:39.518
Excuse the boy, Nathaniel.

25:39.640 --> 25:42.393
No, there's naught to excuse.

25:45.640 --> 25:47.199
Oh, look.

25:47.320 --> 25:50.551
Take that one home.
Cook it for your supper.

25:50.680 --> 25:52.193
It's...

25:52.320 --> 25:53.879
It's the cooking.

25:54.000 --> 25:58.312
Huh. He can catch 'em by the dozen,
but he can't skin and gut 'em for toffee.

25:59.560 --> 26:01.790
Well, it's time you learned, sir.

26:18.160 --> 26:20.549
Here. You have a go.

26:27.080 --> 26:28.309
No, like this.

26:34.120 --> 26:35.394
That's it.

26:51.480 --> 26:54.313
When Robin was just born, I was, erm...

26:54.440 --> 26:56.795
heating his milk on the stove and...

26:58.160 --> 26:59.912
...I was very tired, you see.

27:08.800 --> 27:11.918
I'm sorry for running, Miss Sumner.

27:14.280 --> 27:15.190
From the market.

27:15.320 --> 27:17.357
It's none of my business.

27:18.600 --> 27:19.874
You'd already done plenty.

27:23.360 --> 27:26.352
Well, perhaps you'll see fit
to call me Prudence.

27:27.440 --> 27:29.192
Pru, if it's preferred.

27:34.880 --> 27:36.553
I like Prudence.

27:44.640 --> 27:46.392
(WIND WHISTLES)

27:46.520 --> 27:48.796
Was it your father
who taught you to fish?

27:50.200 --> 27:51.395
No.

27:55.200 --> 27:56.759
The man who raised us...

27:58.080 --> 28:00.356
...my brother and me, he, erm...

28:01.840 --> 28:03.797
...he was not my father.

28:05.280 --> 28:06.270
Was he kind?

28:09.800 --> 28:11.757
For a time.

28:14.320 --> 28:16.391
My papa was, before.

28:18.040 --> 28:20.953
He was a farmer, see.
We...we had a farm.

28:21.080 --> 28:22.798
Where was that?

28:22.920 --> 28:24.911
Another country.

28:26.200 --> 28:28.111
Far away.

28:35.840 --> 28:37.751
We had tulips.

28:38.800 --> 28:40.074
Poppies.

28:41.320 --> 28:43.357
Yellow stonecrop.

28:45.480 --> 28:46.709
Meadow of...

28:48.000 --> 28:49.513
...pink cornflower...

28:52.840 --> 28:54.592
...and bush crickets sang
in the mint fields

28:54.720 --> 28:58.111
and leaf beetles was like...

29:00.520 --> 29:03.114
...like jewels on the corn blades.

29:07.400 --> 29:08.390
I was happy-

29:11.080 --> 29:12.275
I think, erm...

29:13.680 --> 29:15.637
...I always would have been happy.

29:18.360 --> 29:19.555
Why did you leave?

29:24.440 --> 29:26.477
Men came with fire...

29:27.800 --> 29:29.154
...burned the farm...

29:30.840 --> 29:32.274
...burned our home...

29:33.600 --> 29:34.829
...and the village.

29:36.400 --> 29:37.595
Why?

29:37.720 --> 29:40.155
Well, they came to kill
all our people,

29:40.280 --> 29:42.032
COS We was...

29:42.160 --> 29:44.629
We was different to 'em, you see?

29:47.120 --> 29:49.111
Papa's blood was still on the tulips

29:49.240 --> 29:51.516
and...and the men, they was...

29:54.560 --> 29:55.959
...they was laughing.

29:56.080 --> 29:58.390
(WIND WHISTLES)

29:58.520 --> 30:00.318
Mama ran with us to the cart...

30:02.760 --> 30:04.797
...put us under burlap.

30:07.240 --> 30:09.709
It was dark.

30:12.920 --> 30:15.070
Just screams and hooves.

30:23.280 --> 30:25.078
Who did this?

30:30.720 --> 30:32.074
My brother is...

30:33.480 --> 30:35.437
- He is protective.
- Caleb?

30:35.560 --> 30:37.312
He cares for his family but...

30:38.920 --> 30:41.196
...when he drinks, his...his temper...

30:50.920 --> 30:53.753
Caleb blames himself for Mother.

30:56.080 --> 30:59.311
When I fell pregnant,
he held my arm to the stove and...

31:01.520 --> 31:04.751
It was only because
he was scared he'd lose me too.

31:09.240 --> 31:11.754
He's a good boy.

31:11.880 --> 31:14.315
Nathaniel, he's a...he's a good boy.

31:14.440 --> 31:16.397
He loves me, and...

31:17.400 --> 31:19.277
...I love him.

31:22.120 --> 31:24.919
Right, I...I'd best get back.

31:27.160 --> 31:29.470
(WIND WHISTLES)

31:30.920 --> 31:32.194
Thank you for...

31:34.720 --> 31:36.757
...your company, Prudence.

31:42.520 --> 31:43.715
We're...

31:43.840 --> 31:44.910
You are...

31:47.080 --> 31:49.071
...very kind.

31:50.200 --> 31:52.476
You do not need to be so alone,
Nathaniel.

31:58.200 --> 32:00.191
(WIND WHISTLES)

32:10.000 --> 32:12.435
Would you care for a biscuit
with your tea, Mr Dove?

32:12.560 --> 32:16.235
No, thank you, and I apologise
once more for the hour,

32:16.360 --> 32:18.636
but I felt this was a matter
best not delayed.

32:20.720 --> 32:22.677
Miss Reid.

32:22.800 --> 32:25.679
When you chose to give me
that letter from your father,

32:25.800 --> 32:28.110
you performed a noble act
for the policing of this borough.

32:28.240 --> 32:30.038
Please excuse my question, but...

32:32.080 --> 32:33.832
...do you regret that noble act?

32:33.960 --> 32:36.156
Regret it?

32:36.280 --> 32:40.239
Well, fugitive he may be,
but Mr Reid remains your father.

32:42.000 --> 32:43.752
He does, but...

32:45.120 --> 32:47.350
...I did what I felt was right,

32:47.480 --> 32:51.030
even though what is right
is not always what is easy.

32:53.120 --> 32:56.556
I would just like to know the truth,
Mr Dove, once and for all.

32:58.160 --> 32:59.355
Thank you, Miss Reid.

33:00.600 --> 33:03.433
You will perhaps understand
the necessity of my questioning

33:03.560 --> 33:05.392
and my satisfaction at your answer

33:05.520 --> 33:08.592
when I explain
the purpose of my visit.

33:08.720 --> 33:12.475
Mr Drummond,
I wish to offer you a promotion.

33:12.600 --> 33:14.591
Ohh...

33:14.720 --> 33:17.360
Oh, Mr Dove, I...I don't know what...

33:17.480 --> 33:19.153
I mean...to say thank you.

33:19.280 --> 33:20.793
No gratitude required.

33:20.920 --> 33:23.594
It would be dereliction of my duty
to permit abilities such as yours

33:23.720 --> 33:25.631
to go undernourished and unrewarded,

33:25.760 --> 33:27.478
Inspector Drummond.

33:27.600 --> 33:28.749
Miss Reid, a toast.

33:28.880 --> 33:30.075
Yes, of course.

33:31.520 --> 33:33.909
I see great things ahead for you,
Samuel Drummond.

33:34.040 --> 33:37.078
Mr Shine may be the present of
Leman Street, but you are its future.

33:37.200 --> 33:39.157
I expect the Yard itself
shall be calling before long.

33:39.280 --> 33:40.350
In fact, I shall see to it.

33:40.480 --> 33:42.710
Of course,
there will be a raise in wage

33:42.840 --> 33:46.310
commensurate with your new standing,
which I expect may come useful

33:46.440 --> 33:50.320
for young sweethearts perhaps
considering their own home and, well...

33:52.280 --> 33:53.953
...to your future.

33:58.400 --> 34:00.311
Demotion?

34:01.800 --> 34:03.598
Sir? Mr Shine?

34:03.720 --> 34:06.075
Oh, it is, Thatcher.

34:06.200 --> 34:08.554
- It very much so is.
- The bloody desk, sir?

34:08.679 --> 34:11.069
Watch your tongue, Desk Sergeant.

34:11.199 --> 34:15.831
The good Commissioner Dove
has high hopes for Drummond,

34:15.960 --> 34:20.795
and the good Inspector Shine
has low, very low hopes, for you.

34:20.920 --> 34:22.274
(GRUNTS)

34:22.400 --> 34:25.552
So, get out of
that peacocking ponce frock

34:25.679 --> 34:28.513
and into that there tunic.

34:30.280 --> 34:32.429
Get to it, Desk Sergeant!

34:50.440 --> 34:51.429
Thank you, Gustus.

34:51.560 --> 34:53.437
I would not have you
without entertainments...

34:58.160 --> 35:02.438
...though perhaps you have not been so
without entertainments as I supposed.

35:13.280 --> 35:14.509
Miss Sumner.

35:14.640 --> 35:15.914
Miss Sumner?

35:16.040 --> 35:17.997
Yes. The fish-seller's daughter.

35:19.480 --> 35:22.393
Mr Sumner is dead, Gustus.

35:22.520 --> 35:25.194
No, I...I never.

35:25.320 --> 35:27.675
He was...he was poorly, is all,

35:27.800 --> 35:31.395
and she...she was kind.

35:31.520 --> 35:33.033
Kind, is she?

35:33.160 --> 35:35.151
How often has Miss Sumner
afforded you her kindness?

35:35.280 --> 35:37.032
And what have you
afforded her in return?

35:37.160 --> 35:39.515
Naught, Gustus. I...I swear it.

35:41.520 --> 35:44.751
I only helped her with
the, erm...with the fishes, is all.

35:51.080 --> 35:52.559
You...

35:52.680 --> 35:54.557
you went to market?

35:56.640 --> 35:58.153
No, erm...I meant...

35:58.280 --> 35:59.998
Do not lie to me!

36:03.280 --> 36:04.918
Forgive me, Gustus.

36:08.760 --> 36:11.798
This life, however...

36:14.040 --> 36:15.633
...it is a kind of prison.

36:15.760 --> 36:18.036
You talk to me of prison.

36:18.160 --> 36:20.720
But I swear you will
never know a true prison,

36:20.840 --> 36:22.194
because if you are found
and caught for what you've done,

36:22.320 --> 36:24.197
your feet shall scarcely
scrape a cell-room floor

36:24.320 --> 36:26.789
before they dangle through
the noose-man's trap.

36:27.880 --> 36:29.871
And what do you think
would become of me?

36:31.040 --> 36:32.553
Would you cheerily see me
on a rope beside you,

36:32.680 --> 36:34.796
when all I sought was
to keep my brother safe?

36:35.920 --> 36:36.955
I only wanted...

36:37.080 --> 36:38.718
You want a girl? I can get you a girl!

36:38.840 --> 36:40.990
- No, it's not like...
- But you talk to me!

36:41.120 --> 36:42.838
Not some scale-fingered barrow-wailer.

36:42.960 --> 36:44.951
No, not that. Prudence is not...

36:45.080 --> 36:47.549
I asked. Is even that too much
for you to afford me,

36:47.680 --> 36:49.318
while I endeavour
to clean up the blood

36:49.440 --> 36:51.158
with which you spattered Whitechapel?

36:59.880 --> 37:01.757
(SIGHS)

37:05.280 --> 37:07.317
To keep you safe, is all.

37:09.600 --> 37:11.591
Don't you see that, brother?

37:15.040 --> 37:17.509
I see it, Gustus.

37:22.920 --> 37:24.194
I see it.

37:26.440 --> 37:28.397
(TICKING)

37:51.560 --> 37:52.550
Mama!

37:55.120 --> 37:56.235
Come here.

37:56.360 --> 37:59.193
Nathaniel. I did not expect
to see you again.

37:59.320 --> 38:01.960
What? I've been waiting for you.

38:02.080 --> 38:03.115
Do you mean to harm us?

38:03.240 --> 38:04.594
No.

38:04.720 --> 38:06.393
Why would...why would you...

38:06.520 --> 38:09.114
A policeman came here,
Nathaniel, looking for you.

38:09.240 --> 38:10.514
The police?

38:10.640 --> 38:13.280
He said not to go near your cottage
in case you came back.

38:13.400 --> 38:14.310
Go inside, Robin.

38:14.440 --> 38:15.794
What do you mean, came back?

38:15.920 --> 38:17.035
He said you were a fugitive, a danger,

38:17.160 --> 38:19.310
that you'd done things,
that you'd killed.

38:19.440 --> 38:20.635
Prudence...

38:20.760 --> 38:23.479
He said you'd fled.
That's why he came looking for you.

38:23.600 --> 38:24.670
Get away from here!

38:24.800 --> 38:27.792
The police inspector said
you'd pissed off from these parts.

38:27.920 --> 38:29.479
You should have stayed away.

38:30.800 --> 38:32.393
- Caleb...
- You leave us be, you hear me?

38:32.520 --> 38:36.514
- Don't come back here!
- Nathaniel! Please!

38:36.640 --> 38:37.835
Go.

38:41.680 --> 38:43.000
Please.

38:43.120 --> 38:44.713
No.

39:13.640 --> 39:15.392
(CLOCK CHIMES)

39:21.080 --> 39:23.071
(DOG BARKS)

39:23.200 --> 39:24.918
(DOG BARKS)

39:25.040 --> 39:27.680
- Would you like a cup of tea, sir?
- Thank you, Miss Chudleigh.

39:27.800 --> 39:29.916
- (DOG BARKS)
- Where is the boy?

39:30.040 --> 39:32.919
He's at play in the garden
with his animal, sir.

39:33.040 --> 39:35.156
(DOG BARKS)

39:36.880 --> 39:38.871
(DOG BARKS)

39:40.040 --> 39:41.360
- (DOG YELPS)
- Connor!

39:48.600 --> 39:50.591
Miss Chudleigh. Miss Chudleigh!

39:53.400 --> 39:55.755
- Take Connor inside.
- Of course, Mr Dove.

40:02.760 --> 40:04.751
(DOOR CLOSES)

40:08.280 --> 40:11.272
Do you remember the cornfields
after summer rain, Gustus?

40:12.960 --> 40:15.429
And when the sun returned,

40:15.560 --> 40:17.437
everything shining.

40:17.560 --> 40:19.358
All the glittering blades...

40:23.600 --> 40:27.230
...and I would cry at harvest
to see 'em all cut down.

40:29.000 --> 40:31.196
How did you get in here?

40:34.200 --> 40:36.032
I came up a towpath.

40:36.160 --> 40:37.514
Through the hedgerows.

40:39.400 --> 40:41.437
I thought to visit you,

40:41.560 --> 40:43.870
and I found the boy
alone in the garden...

40:46.040 --> 40:47.792
...and see how you looked at us...

40:49.720 --> 40:51.040
...the fear...

40:52.280 --> 40:54.556
...as if I'd ever have it in me
to harm him.

40:55.960 --> 40:59.032
He was helping me choose
some blooms, is all.

41:00.600 --> 41:02.432
Blooms for Miss Sumner.

41:02.560 --> 41:03.834
(DOG BARKS)

41:03.960 --> 41:05.519
What you done, Gustus...

41:08.680 --> 41:10.478
...that was unkind.

41:10.600 --> 41:12.273
It was for your own good, Nathaniel.

41:13.760 --> 41:14.875
And yours.

41:15.000 --> 41:16.559
There is no difference.

41:16.680 --> 41:18.000
You are my brother.

41:19.400 --> 41:21.118
But you are not my keeper.

41:22.560 --> 41:24.915
I will stay away from Whitechapel.

41:25.040 --> 41:29.716
But you, Gustus, you must stay away
from Prudence Sumner.

41:30.920 --> 41:32.149
She is...

41:34.360 --> 41:35.839
She is my friend.

41:39.400 --> 41:40.913
All I ever did...

41:42.080 --> 41:44.594
...was for protection of you.

41:52.160 --> 41:54.151
Thank you for the blooms, Gustus.

41:57.320 --> 41:59.436
Prudence will like 'em.

42:42.960 --> 42:44.997
I didn't think you'd come.

42:45.120 --> 42:46.394
Nor I.

42:51.360 --> 42:53.351
Your brother?

42:53.480 --> 42:54.470
Yeah.

42:56.440 --> 42:58.317
Why would he say
those things about you?

43:00.680 --> 43:03.115
To keep me away from you.

43:05.440 --> 43:06.760
My brother, he is also...

43:09.440 --> 43:10.714
...protective,

43:10.840 --> 43:12.513
and he wants...

43:14.160 --> 43:15.559
...to protect me...

43:17.160 --> 43:19.276
...to protect us both, but...

43:22.720 --> 43:24.438
...he thinks me animal.

43:26.920 --> 43:28.831
Is it true, then,

43:28.960 --> 43:30.280
what he said?

43:33.520 --> 43:34.749
I'm not an animal.

43:40.040 --> 43:42.236
(HE SIGHS)

43:43.800 --> 43:45.950
I don't see an animal, Nathaniel.

43:49.360 --> 43:51.351
I see...

43:51.480 --> 43:54.154
a hurt, lonely boy.

43:59.080 --> 44:01.151
I did not come here to judge.

44:02.200 --> 44:04.999
I do not want Caleb to hurt you no more.

44:05.120 --> 44:07.316
I mean, what if we left this place?

44:08.680 --> 44:09.795
Robin as well.

44:09.920 --> 44:12.878
I can't leave Caleb, Nathaniel.

44:15.000 --> 44:17.674
He was my baby boy and...

44:17.800 --> 44:20.360
and Robin, he needs him,

44:20.480 --> 44:21.595
and...

44:23.600 --> 44:26.479
...Caleb is a good soul.

44:26.600 --> 44:28.273
Sometimes we...

44:31.600 --> 44:34.399
...we can just love someone too much.

44:34.520 --> 44:36.716
(WIND WHISTLES)

45:10.080 --> 45:12.151
Take off your shirt.

45:25.800 --> 45:28.030
That's it.

45:28.160 --> 45:30.117
Stand for me.

45:30.240 --> 45:32.356
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

45:45.600 --> 45:47.079
Beautiful boy.

45:49.240 --> 45:50.753
(SHE SIGHS)

45:50.880 --> 45:52.279
(GASPS)

45:58.480 --> 46:00.471
(SHE MOANS)

46:00.600 --> 46:02.034
(GASPS)

46:25.640 --> 46:28.109
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

46:48.760 --> 46:50.592
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

46:52.760 --> 46:54.671
(SHE MOANS)

46:56.200 --> 46:58.157
(MOANS AND GRUNTS)

47:20.080 --> 47:21.798
It's OK.

47:26.040 --> 47:28.554
Shh. just lie...

47:28.680 --> 47:31.149
Shh. just lie with me.

47:31.280 --> 47:32.270
Yeah.

47:33.600 --> 47:35.989
Come on. That's it.

47:36.120 --> 47:38.111
- (GASPS)
- Yeah.

47:38.240 --> 47:40.550
Shh...

47:53.960 --> 47:55.917
(DOG BARKS)

47:56.040 --> 47:57.519
JACKSON: We'll be gone soon.

47:58.720 --> 48:01.075
I'm sure of it,
and I just wanted you to know that.

48:03.000 --> 48:05.560
You are a funny trio,

48:05.680 --> 48:08.672
you, Mr Reid and your...

48:10.440 --> 48:12.158
...Miss Hart.

48:12.280 --> 48:14.157
You ought to put us on the stage.

48:16.920 --> 48:19.150
There's blood on their hands.

48:21.120 --> 48:23.077
Black in their hearts.

48:24.120 --> 48:25.394
But you...

48:28.800 --> 48:30.393
I remember these hands...

48:33.000 --> 48:35.514
...and the colours of your heart.

48:36.600 --> 48:38.398
I ain't no saint neither, Mimi.

48:43.680 --> 48:47.196
Have you thought what your life will be,
the day you stop running?

48:47.320 --> 48:51.279
I've been running so long,
I can't remember what it's like to stop.

48:56.120 --> 48:58.111
Do you know what makes me angry,
Captain Jackson?

48:58.240 --> 49:02.996
It is that for all your
uncountable faults, deviancies,

49:03.120 --> 49:06.397
downright failings as man
and...and human being...

49:07.760 --> 49:10.115
...when you knocked on my door...

49:11.160 --> 49:13.197
...whenever you knock on my door...

49:15.320 --> 49:18.950
...I feel the best
and most precious part of me leap.

49:20.560 --> 49:23.279
I feel it turn cartwheels in sunlight...

49:25.600 --> 49:29.389
...and the abject, grotty truth
I must contend with

49:29.520 --> 49:33.036
is that I'd rather see my theatre
in ruins with you here...

49:34.160 --> 49:38.552
...than have it a glittering and ecstatic
stage with you far and gone.

49:41.320 --> 49:43.357
I hate you,

49:43.480 --> 49:45.949
Homer, Matthew,

49:46.080 --> 49:48.469
whatever your cursed name is,
I hate you.

49:49.720 --> 49:51.552
I hate you...

49:52.600 --> 49:56.673
...cos when you're in my life,
my life seems electric...

49:58.760 --> 50:00.273
...and then you go...

50:01.400 --> 50:02.959
...and you'll go.

50:04.000 --> 50:07.311
Of that, if nothing else on this Earth,
I am certain...

50:08.480 --> 50:09.675
...and when you go...

50:12.200 --> 50:15.750
...those sunlit cartwheels
will fall once more still and dim.

50:25.520 --> 50:27.830
One day this theatre will
open its doors...

50:29.280 --> 50:30.270
(SNIFFS)

50:30.400 --> 50:31.754
...and I shall try to live at peace

50:31.880 --> 50:34.394
with knowing you shan't
knock on them again.

50:54.720 --> 50:56.677
This tastes very good, Prudence.

50:59.800 --> 51:01.757
Will you show me more fishing,
Nathaniel?

51:01.880 --> 51:03.598
I'm sure Nathaniel's busy, boy.

51:03.720 --> 51:07.429
No, I...erm, of course,
of course, Robin.

51:07.560 --> 51:09.597
I said he was busy.

51:09.720 --> 51:11.836
You stay clear.

51:15.760 --> 51:19.435
Will Nathaniel be helping
on the stall again?

51:21.440 --> 51:23.829
I prefer not to go to Whitechapel.

51:23.960 --> 51:24.995
Why?

51:26.080 --> 51:27.559
I do not care for it.

51:27.680 --> 51:29.637
Is it the Jews?

51:29.760 --> 51:31.671
Do not say such things, Caleb.

51:33.760 --> 51:37.833
Pru tells me you're from abroad.
You're not one of them, are you?

51:37.960 --> 51:39.758
No.

51:39.880 --> 51:41.279
I am not.

51:41.400 --> 51:44.711
Cos I'll tell you
one thing about the Jews.

51:44.840 --> 51:46.717
They won't buy your bloody eels.

51:46.840 --> 51:48.990
(SNIGGERS)

51:50.040 --> 51:53.874
I taught Nathaniel how to cook eel,
just like Father used to.

51:59.080 --> 52:01.151
What else have you taught him?

52:09.320 --> 52:11.675
The flowers are beautiful, Nathaniel.

52:14.360 --> 52:15.919
You're very welcome.

52:19.360 --> 52:21.874
Robin, fill your uncle's cup.

52:23.040 --> 52:24.758
(BOTTLE UNCORKED)

52:24.880 --> 52:26.996
To the top, boy.

52:28.120 --> 52:29.269
Don't waste it!

52:29.400 --> 52:30.674
Caleb.

52:30.800 --> 52:33.679
Go to bed, little one.
Now leave that. There you go.

52:36.760 --> 52:38.558
You've had plenty.

52:44.960 --> 52:47.839
Why is he here?

52:49.080 --> 52:51.230
Nathaniel is our friend

52:51.360 --> 52:52.794
and our guest.

52:56.440 --> 52:59.353
Welcome, friend.

53:09.880 --> 53:10.870
Nathaniel...

53:13.840 --> 53:16.673
(WHISPERS) Forgive him. Forgive him.

53:16.800 --> 53:19.314
He's...he is a good boy.

53:26.800 --> 53:29.076
He will sleep soon,

53:29.200 --> 53:31.714
and I will come to you, OK?

53:40.160 --> 53:41.798
(DOOR CLOSES)

53:54.960 --> 53:57.076
(GASPS)

54:00.960 --> 54:02.189
(CRIES)

54:02.320 --> 54:04.231
- Take him to your tit...
- Please, no!

54:04.360 --> 54:05.839
-...did you?
- No more!

54:09.840 --> 54:12.036
Nathaniel! No!

54:12.160 --> 54:14.993
Nathaniel! No! Nathaniel!

54:15.120 --> 54:17.475
- No, please!
- It ain't right, Prudence!

54:17.600 --> 54:19.876
What he does! It ain't right!

54:20.000 --> 54:22.514
Shh, shh.

54:22.640 --> 54:23.994
Shh.

54:24.120 --> 54:26.316
I know. I know.

54:26.440 --> 54:28.431
Please listen to me.

54:28.560 --> 54:31.678
He is...he is my brother...

54:34.520 --> 54:36.397
...and he's...

54:37.840 --> 54:41.151
He's...Robin's father.

54:42.640 --> 54:44.313
- Wha...
- Yeah.

54:44.440 --> 54:46.113
- What?
- Yeah.

54:46.240 --> 54:48.231
- No.
- OK. Please.

